answers.answer: Protein in urine can be a sign of UTI or bladder infection. Later in pregnancy, if it is accompanied by high blood pressure, it is a strong indicator of preeclampsia. If not, then your urine will be sent off for further testing. If all is normal, they will want to monitor you a bit more closely to make sure no other complications develop.
